## 3. The Role of Insurance Companies and Cost-Shifting

Insurance companies play a complex role in healthcare pricing. Hospitals often charge higher prices to private insurers to compensate for lower reimbursements from Medicare, Medicaid, or uninsured patients. This cost-shifting contributes to inflated bills for insured patients ([Quora, 2018](https://www.quora.com/Are-US-hospital-bills-inflated-due-to-insurance-companies)).

Furthermore, the multi-payer insurance system increases administrative burdens, as hospitals and providers must navigate numerous billing protocols and reimbursement policies, adding to overhead costs ([Advisory Board, 2018](https://www.advisory.com/daily-briefing/2018/07/23/administrative-costs)).

